# =============================================================================
# Agent Health - Environment Variables
# =============================================================================
#
# Most users need NO configuration to get started!
# Just run: npx agent-health run -t demo-otel-001 -a demo
#
# Set variables below for additional features:
# - AWS credentials for Claude Code and Bedrock judge
# - OpenSearch storage to persist results
# - OpenSearch observability for agent traces
#

# =============================================================================
# AWS CREDENTIALS (usually auto-detected from ~/.aws/credentials)
# =============================================================================
# Required for: Claude Code agent, Bedrock judge
# If you've run `aws configure`, these are already set!

# AWS_PROFILE=Bedrock
# AWS_REGION=us-west-2

# =============================================================================
# OPENSEARCH STORAGE (optional - for saving results)
# =============================================================================
# Without storage: Results shown in terminal, no persistence
# With storage: Results saved, viewable in UI, history tracking

# OPENSEARCH_STORAGE_ENDPOINT=https://your-cluster.amazonaws.com
# OPENSEARCH_STORAGE_USERNAME=admin
# OPENSEARCH_STORAGE_PASSWORD=your_password

# =============================================================================
# OPENSEARCH OBSERVABILITY (optional - for agent traces)
# =============================================================================
# Only needed if using ML-Commons agent with tracing enabled

# OPENSEARCH_LOGS_ENDPOINT=https://your-cluster.amazonaws.com
# OPENSEARCH_LOGS_USERNAME=admin
# OPENSEARCH_LOGS_PASSWORD=your_password
# OPENSEARCH_LOGS_TRACES_INDEX=otel-v1-apm-span-*
# OPENSEARCH_LOGS_INDEX=ml-commons-logs-*

# =============================================================================
# ADVANCED: Server Configuration (rarely needed)
# =============================================================================
# VITE_BACKEND_PORT=4001
# BEDROCK_MODEL_ID=us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929-v1:0
